headline: BlackRock wins 67% support for pay as CEO Fink assures on global economy
summary: (Reuters) -Top asset manager BlackRock said on Thursday that 67% of votes cast at its annual meeting were in support of its executive pay, a modest gain over last year, as CEO Larry Fink offered assurances about the state of the global economy and defended the company's course on environmental and social issues.  Proxy adviser Institutional Shareholder Services had recommended that investors vote against the pay of top executives including Fink, who received $30.8 million in 2024.  ISS said BlackRock did not sufficiently address investors' compensation concerns in 2023, when only 59% of votes cast supported the pay of top executives, citing issues like a lack of clarity on pay determinations.
